
1. Define the topology in mininet. In this example is defined in mininet_topology.py file.
1.2. Put the IP of the controller

2. Start OpenNaaS
2.1. Create the openflowswitch resources and the genericNetwork resource.
	resource:create /opt/opennaas/utils/examples/NFV-VRF/s1.descriptor
	resource:create /opt/opennaas/utils/examples/NFV-VRF/s2.descriptor
	resource:create /opt/opennaas/utils/examples/NFV-VRF/s3.descriptor
	resource:create /opt/opennaas/utils/examples/NFV-VRF/s4.descriptor
	resource:create /opt/opennaas/utils/examples/NFV-VRF/ofnet1.descriptor
   Take into account that the ofnet1 descriptor contains topology. This topology is read from the topology.xml file
2.2. Define the context of the openflow switch. DPID of the switch and the controller IP
	protocols:context -p protocol.floodlight.switchid=00:00:00:00:00:00:00:01 openflowswitch:s1 floodlight noauth http://localhost:8080
	protocols:context -p protocol.floodlight.switchid=00:00:00:00:00:00:00:02 openflowswitch:s2 floodlight noauth http://localhost:8080
	protocols:context -p protocol.floodlight.switchid=00:00:00:00:00:00:00:03 openflowswitch:s3 floodlight noauth http://localhost:8080
	protocols:context -p protocol.floodlight.switchid=00:00:00:00:00:00:00:04 openflowswitch:s4 floodlight noauth http://localhost:8080
2.3. Start the resources
	resource:start openflowswitch:s1
	resource:start openflowswitch:s2
	resource:start openflowswitch:s3
	resource:start openflowswitch:s4
	resource:start genericnetwork:ofnet1

3. Start Openflow controller
3.1. Both Floodlight and OpenDaylight controllers requires a NFV bundle

4. Start Mininet
4.1. Use the example topology (mininet_topology.py file). ./mininet_topology.py
4.2. Start ShellInABox script

5. Start the GUI with Tomcat
